title: Bikes for Kids/University of Utah Omnium
USU Criterium and Team Time Trial
description: Utah State University is hosting its first ever road racing events. These races will be open to both collegiate and public racers and will include a morning criterium and a afternoon team time trial.
course:
The Criterium will be held in a new business development in North Logan on 200 West and 2500 North. Just North of Mount Logan Off-Road. The course is almost 1.8 miles long.

The Team Time Trial will be held up Blacksmith Fork Canyon. It will begin at Hardware Ranch head downhill to mile marker 11. Teams will then turn around and finish at Hardware Ranch. Total race distance will be 20 miles.
registration: Registration will be held at the starting line of each race and begin 1 hour prior to the start of the first race.
notes: Entry Fees will $25 per event or $40 for both. Collegiate cycling discounts available with collegiate license.
directions:
From Utah State University:

Head North on Main Street for the morning criterium and turn left on 2500 North. Then take your first right onto 200 West. Park in the Street. 

Head South on Main Street for the afternoon Team Time Trial. Stay left (on Main Street) at the Highway 89 junction. Travel South for about 6 miles after the Junction and then turn left on Blacksmith Fork Road. Follow Blacksmith Fork Road for 15 miles to Hardware Ranch. Registration will be on the left.

UCI BMX Great Salt Lake Nationals
Pivot/BH Demo
description:
2010 Pivot and BH Demo day presented by Millcreek Bicycles.
August 29th 2010 10:00am-4:00pm
course: Mountain riders will ride shore line north the Red Butte Canyon and back. Road riders will ride up Emigration Canyon and back. Both rides will take approximately 45 minutes to an hour.
registration:

Must have a valid drivers license and credit card.
Must sign a waiver. Helmets are required.
